result.name: Minh & Kok

reviews.text: Terrible service from one of the male waiters. Lack of vegetarian options so I politely asked if they could make one of the noodles vegetarian (all it takes is simply to remove the spring rolls) he rudely replied “no, cannot” and that was that. I’ve received better service from cheaper establishments at a fraction of the price. Not worth going at all.
Good location, nice setting and well designed restaurant. But the food was less than mediocre. Soups were lacking flavor and depth. Who the pho puts an egg in a bowl of pho?

Was there this afternoon and took a lunch set with rare beef pho and snacks platter. Price was very reasonable. The platter was good, but the beef pho could perhaps be better if they got the beef slices thin and the soup slightly more tasty. Service was good though, and the setting was simple but comfortable.
Not very traditional viet food but good value overall.
Good, not great. And price is reasonable for its location. Don't expect true local authentic Vietnamese food. It's westernized, fusion taste. Still a good choice though.
